6: Hi. Is this place still taking orders?
9: We sure are. What can I get for you?
12:
Three servings of your most popular
dish.
21:
I don't know. It's just that she seems...
familiar.
31:
What in the world? This place is still
open?
35: What do you think you're doing?
39:
I fail to comprehend the logic
behind your actions.
41:
Logic? I knocked that hog swill off
the table 'cause I wanted to. How's
that for logic?
44:
Think you could keep it down? Your
noise is spoiling the wine.
49: I said I want to drink in peace.
52:
What's with the ears, huh? I never
seen anything like them.
53:
You wanted to drink? ...There. Lap it
up like the mutt you are.
57: Alk, you need not draw your sword.
67: Let me give you a warning.
68:
Not a soul alive will heed the cries of
the wicked. The only thing that will
answer... is death.
71: The hell is that supposed to—
84:
You've painted crosshairs on this
place! All those times I turned the
other cheek... They don't mean
anything now!
86:
Has that man been here before?
Who was he?
89:
There's a whole group of
them—failed adventurers from
Palpebra. They've formed a kind of
gang, and claimed this whole area
as their turf.
90:
Dammit! I don't have the money to
hire one of those Guild bodyguards!
94:
There is no need for that. We will go
speak with this "gang."
97:
Will you come with us—er... What
shall I call you?
101:
Mormia. And I'm going to have to
turn you down.
104:
I'll put out fires that are near me, but
I don't go running into them.
107:
Then I will not press you. Alk, will you
lend me your strength?
113:
Of course! Our dinner's on the line
here.
122:
No... It seems she was not so callous
after all.
128: For the last time, we're here to TALK!
147: Thanks! You really saved my hide.
155:
I'm not here to save you. I'm here
because I have questions.
161: You're not from this world, are you?
165:
We're celebrating! Free meals on me
ALL DAY!
168:
Then you too are a wanderer in
strange lands...
171:
I was apparently born in a place
called the Elven Woods.
177:
Everything I know about those
woods, I learned from my dad. He's
human. And that was grounds for
getting us banished when I was too
young to even understand what
was going on.
179:
But I can still faintly remember silver
trees...
184:
Do you want to live in the Elven
Woods again?
186:
I don't know about that... But I'd like
to see it one more time.
190:
Then come with us. I am certain we'll
find your home again.
194:
...I never could've guessed you were
traveling between worlds. I still find it
hard to believe.
198:
But thank you. As long as we're
together, I'll keep you safe. This
sword isn't just for show.
203:
That would be super appreciated.
Welcome to the team, Mormia!
